===Alternative forms===
* In Korean [[hanja]], the upper component of the character is written {{l|mul|八}} instead of {{l|mul|丷}}, which is also the historical form found in the [[w:Kangxi dictionary|Kangxi dictionary]].
* A [[w:CJK Compatibility Ideographs|CJK compatibility ideograph]] exists at <code>U+FA17</code> for the historical form found in the [[w:Kangxi dictionary|Kangxi dictionary]] which contains {{l|mul|八}} as its upper component.
* A [[w:CJK Compatibility Ideographs|CJK compatibility ideograph]] exists at <code>U+FAA6</code> for the alternative [[hanja]] used in North Korea which contains {{l|mul|丷}} as its upper component.

